<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="123" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d123">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the British Prime Minister</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Churchill</hi></persName>)<note n="82" type="source" xml:id="d123fn82">Copy of telegram obtained from the Franklin D.
                                    Roosevelt Library, Hyde Park, N.Y. Copy sent to the Secretary of
                                    State by President Roosevelt on June 30.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-12">12 June
                                    1944</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>560. Personal for the Former Naval Person.<note n="83" xml:id="d123fn83">Code name for Winston S. Churchill.</note>
                                Your 700.<note n="84" xml:id="d123fn84">Dated June 11, <ref target="#pg_118">p. 118</ref>.</note> I am in agreement with
                                your proposal in paragraph 7 of subject message.</p>
                            <p>We must be careful to make it clear that we are not establishing any
                                post war spheres of influence.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>